    Kenneth Roman will leave the Ogilvy Group to become an executive vice 
president with American Express. Some industry executives think Roman's 
departure resulted from tension with Martin Sorrell, head of the company that 
successfully took over the Ogilvy Group. Clients and analysts have mixed 
feelings about whether Roman's successor, Graham Phillips, will be able to 
turn the Ogilvy Group around.


